<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8478> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8478" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 731, footnote 61" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8176> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8176" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 186. In MRR 1.370-371, refer also to Liv. 40.36.10.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2467> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2467" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "P. Cornelius Scipio (Africani f.) succeeded Sp. Postumius Albinus. Liv. 40.42.13. On Postumius, see Münzer, APF 213ff." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2364> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2364" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sp. Postumius Albinus succeeded Cn. Cornelius Lentulus. Liv. 39.45.8. On Postumius, see Münzer, APF 213." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2306> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2306" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 39.6.1, cf. 23.1; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 122, 456f.; Plin. NH 33.138; Eutrop. 4.5; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod. Both Consuls were assigned Liguria (Liv. 39.20.2), but Albinus was wholly, and Philippus for most of the year, occupied with the investigation{371} of the Bacchanalian mysteries (Liv. 39.8-19; Val. Max. 6.3.7; cf. CIL 1\n     .2.581- ILS 18; Cic. Leg. 2.37; Val. Max. 1.3.1). Philippus raided the territory of the Apuan Ligurians and suffered heavy losses (Liv. 39.20; Oros. 4.20.26). On Postumius, see Münzer, APF 213." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2242> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2242" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Became Pr. Urb. only when Fabius Pictor was kept in Rome (Liv. 37.51, cf. 57.4). See SIG\n     612, his letter to the Delphians; and Holleaux, BCH 54 (1930) 1-38; Roussel, BCH 56 (1932) 21; Daux, Delphes 262. See also, Münzer, APF 213." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2237> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2237" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elections: Liv. 37.47.8 Provinces and armies Liv. 37.50.8-12." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2175> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2175" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "May be the Aedile before whom Furius Chresimus disproved the charge of luring his neighbors' crops away by magic (Piso fr. 33 Peter). Livy does not record the Aediles of this year, and the Consul of 334 seems too early. See Seidel 77." .
